net.markenwerk.utils.json.parser

Enum JsonParserMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<JsonParserMode>
      • net.markenwerk.utils.json.parser.JsonParserMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<JsonParserMode>

    public enum JsonParserMode
extends Enum<JsonParserMode>
    A JsonParserMode is a configuration flag that modifies the execution of a JsonSourcePullParser or a JsonSourcePushParser.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      MULTI_DOCUMENT_MODE
      Allows a JsonSource to contain successive JSON documents.
      STRICT_STRUCT_MODE
      Requires that the JSON document contains either a JSON array or a JSON object, but no other JSON value, as required in the now obsolete RFC 4627

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • MULTI_DOCUMENT_MODE

        public static final JsonParserMode MULTI_DOCUMENT_MODE
        Allows a JsonSource to contain successive JSON documents. May be useful to stream through a log file that contains appended JSON documents or to process a server response where the server sends multiple JSON documents through a persistent connection.

      • STRICT_STRUCT_MODE

        public static final JsonParserMode STRICT_STRUCT_MODE
        Requires that the JSON document contains either a JSON array or a JSON object, but no other JSON value, as required in the now obsolete RFC 4627
